{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Sym_states.Pure_fun</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Sym_states","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Pure_fun","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>State model component of pure functions. A piece of state represents a function `f()` that returns a value in a certain set. It is quite similar to the agreement algebra, except that there is no allocation, there necessarily exists a value, and if we don't know it, we instantiate it on read/consumption.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Codom\"><a href=\"#module-Codom\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Codom/index.html\">Codom</a></span><span> (<a href=\"Codom/argument-1-Symex/index.html\">Symex</a> : <a href=\"../../Symex/module-type-Base/index.html\">Symex.Base</a>) : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>FIXME: This is almost verbatim the same thing as the input of excl</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Make\"><a href=\"#module-Make\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Make/index.html\">Make</a></span><span> (<a href=\"Make/argument-1-Symex/index.html\">Symex</a> : <a href=\"../../Symex/module-type-Base/index.html\">Symex.Base</a>) (<a href=\"Make/argument-2-C/index.html\">C</a> : <a href=\"Codom/module-type-S/index.html\">Codom(Symex).S</a>) : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div>"}